claim.claim-text:
1. A method for producing an image noise table having statistics in a particular metric format for use with image processing algorithms, comprising the steps of: 
a) gathering estimated noise statistics of noise estimates provided from image capture medium, or image capture device(s), or combinations thereof which are in one or more metric formats; 
b) transforming the gathered noise statistics from their metric format(s) to a second metric format useable in the image noise table; 
c) transforming the second metric format noise statistics based upon the spatial qualities of image capture to a format for use in the image noise table; and 
d) providing the image noise table using the transformed second metric format statistics.
